President Cyril Ramaphosa's legal team is hoping the courts will help protect their client's financial information. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa's legal team is hoping the courts will help protect their client's financial information. The team has apparently written to the North Gauteng High Court to request that details linked to banks accounts intended for the CR17 campaign not be made public. The lawyers asked that documents obtained by Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane only be made available to the court and to the respondents. READ: Ramaphosa CR17 emails leaked News24 on Saturday published details of what it says are leaked emails between Ramaphosa and his campaign manager ahead of his ANC presidential campaign of 2017. Mkhwebane made reference to emails when she found that Ramaphosa misled Parliament about the source of the Bosasa donation to his campaign. READ: ANC rubbishes Ramaphosa 'leaked emails' Mkhwebane has not said how the emails she received were obtained. The president is currently challenging Mkhwebane's report.